Here's a single HTML file demonstrating a directed graph using JavaScript:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Directed Graph Visualization</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        #graph-container {
            width: 600px;
            height: 400px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            margin: 20px 0;
            position: relative;
        }
        .node {
            position: absolute;
            width: 40px;
            height: 40px;
            border-radius: 50%;
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: white;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
